gem "jekyll-bmepy"

### Injecting css and scss in my Jekyll template

#### First, insert css in the html file
```
{% include "css/styles.scss" %}
```

#### Second, inject the corresponding css file in my assets/css folder

> ❗️ I don't want to use `assets/_scss/styles.scss` for the below because it'll inject in my `frontmatter`

```
{% include _scss/styles.css %}
```


### Use Jekyll-sass to compile css

```
/bin/sass --style  compressed --source-map --out-dir assets/css --source-map-dest sass_map.map
